<subSubSection id="C3126579215AFFF7FF221F66FE6FFAB1" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF221F66FE6FFAB1" blockId="8.[151,1437,1123,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF221F66FE8FFB99" bold="true" box="[151,273,1123,1149]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF221F66FE94FB99" bold="true" box="[151,266,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B17215AFFF7FED81F66FE4DFB99" box="[365,467,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.41" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="14.1">14.1 mm</quantity>
. Width 
<quantity id="4CF09B17215AFFF7FD921F66FDE1FB99" box="[551,639,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" unit="mm" value="8.1">8.1 mm</quantity>
. Body dorsally green, corium brownish-green; beneath greenish-yellow (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FF151F82FE83FB45" box="[160,285,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1G–H</figureCitation>
). Tegument densely punctuated, punctures on distal margin of pronotum and scutellum black on dark spots, not forming lines like in 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215AFFF7FE481FAEFD15FB20" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[509,651,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricava" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FE481FAEFD15FB20" box="[509,651,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">G. nigricava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FD211FAEFD52FB21" bold="true" box="[660,716,1195,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215AFFF7FD211FAEFD52FB21" box="[660,716,1195,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Disc of pronotum with green punctures on green spots slightly darker than the background (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE601FCAFDB3FB0D" box="[469,557,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
). Humeral angles projection short, dentiform.Anterior half of the costal margin of corium with punctures on black spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FDC11FF6FD50FAE9" box="[628,718,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
); hypocostal ridge with black punctures. Legs with large black spots (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FF571E12FEA0FAD5" box="[226,318,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Connexival segment VII with margin and punctures black. Distal part of the genital cup deeply excavated and black (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE3F1E3EFE7AFAB1" box="[394,484,1338,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215AFFF7FF721E5AFE19F871" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF721E5AFC56F991" blockId="8.[151,1437,1123,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721E5AFECAFA9D" bold="true" box="[199,340,1375,1401]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721E5AFED3FA9D" bold="true" box="[199,333,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head wider than long (1.5 times). Antennae with only two segments lasting, both greenish-yellow, with small black spots. Thorax: Pronotum wider than long (3 times); cicatrices delimited by grooves, not punctuated. Beneath thoracic segments densely and irregularly punctured, punctures mostly concolorous; some punctures on propleura on green spots slightly darker than the background (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FCD51ECEFC25FA01" box="[864,955,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Evaporatorium concolorous, dull, gently grooved, not spotted; lateral area rounded with concolorous punctures (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FC661EEAFBB1F9ED" box="[979,1071,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Metasternal process greenishyellow; anterior bifurcation with arms strongly acuminate; not spotted (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FC731D16FBBEF9C9" box="[966,1056,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,191,1824]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[171,1416,181,1841]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Grammedessa. A–B: G. hamata comb.n. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view. C–D: G. nigricava sp.n. C: Dorsal view. D: Ventral view. E–F: G. longispina sp.n. E: Dorsal view. F: Ventral view. G–H: G. fundicava sp.n. G: Dorsal view. H: Ventral view. I–J: G. graciligramma sp.n. I: Dorsal view. J: Ventral view. K–L: G. stichtocephala sp.n. K: Dorsal view. L: Ventral view. M–N: G. acalyptoprocta sp.n. M: Dorsal view. N: Ventral view. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: connexivum densely punctuated; segments III–VI medially with a callus barely visible. Ventrally shagreen, sparsely punctured, punctures concolorous; one trichobothrium in line and the other lateral to spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF721D7BFE19F871" blockId="8.[151,1437,1123,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721D7BFE9CF97D" bold="true" box="[199,258,1662,1689]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FEA11D7AFEC4F97D" box="[276,346,1662,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dark yellow, elongated (1.3 times); dorsal rim rounded, brown, not projected over the genital cup, except medially slightly projected over proctiger (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FCC11DA6FC50F959" box="[884,974,1698,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles slightly developed and somewhat tumid. Genital cup with a secondary deeper rounded excavation close to the ventral rim (visible as a rounded light spot on 
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE1D1DEEFD9DF8E1" box="[424,515,1770,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Parameres with base cylindrical, anterior process large and triangular, posterior process short and triangular (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE6F1C0AFDACF8CD" box="[474,562,1806,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger elongated (1.3 times), somewhat excavated laterally; thin carina on most of the posterior face (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE741C36FD84F8A9" box="[449,538,1842,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim widely opened; expansions small, tumid, and rounded almost fused with posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE7D1C52FDBFF895" box="[456,545,1878,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface convex beneath posterolateral angles; dark punctures near the ventral rim (
<figureCitation id="13332A77215AFFF7FE971C7EFEE4F871" box="[290,378,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1773,1797]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,449,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-111@9.[156,1431,417,1750]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of G. fundicava sp.n. A: Pygophore in dorsal view. B: Pygophore in ventral view. C: Pygophore in posterior view. Scale = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500683/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215AFFF7FF721C9BFEE6F83A" pageId="8" pageNumber="219" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215AFFF7FF721C9BFEE6F83A" blockId="8.[151,1437,1123,2014]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721C9BFED7F85D" bold="true" box="[199,329,1950,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF721C9BFEDCF85D" bold="true" box="[199,322,1950,1977]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Named by the deep rounded excavation on the genital cup. From the Latin. 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FB701C9AFA87F85D" box="[1221,1305,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Fundus</emphasis>
(deep) and 
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215AFFF7FF221CC6FF43F839" box="[151,221,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="219">Cavus</emphasis>
(excavation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3126579215BFFF6FF721B92FCA2FE82" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB736F2215BFFF6FF721B92FB64FF1D" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FF721B92FED7FF55" bold="true" box="[199,329,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FF721B92FEDCFF55" bold="true" box="[199,322,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species shares with 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215BFFF6FDC01B92FCDCFF55" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[629,834,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graciligramma" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FDC01B92FCDCFF55" box="[629,834,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">G. graciligramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FCF91B92FC1AFF55" bold="true" box="[844,900,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215BFFF6FCF91B92FC1AFF55" box="[844,900,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215BFFF6FC751B92FBCFFF54" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[960,1105,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricava" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FC751B92FBCFFF54" box="[960,1105,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">G. nigricava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FBEE1B92FB0CFF55" bold="true" box="[1115,1170,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215BFFF6FBEE1B92FB0CFF55" box="[1115,1170,151,177]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the genital cup deeply excavated close to the ventral rim. But the rounded deeper excavation is unique to 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D71215BFFF6FB8F1BBEFB55FF31" authority="Silva &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Da Silva &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1082,1227,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Grammedessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fundicava" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FB8F1BBEFB55FF31" box="[1082,1227,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">G. fundicava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97CEAE0215BFFF6FB661BBEFA94FF31" bold="true" box="[1235,1290,187,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F579B215BFFF6FB661BBEFA94FF31" box="[1235,1290,187,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; ventral side of abdomen shagreen and sparsely punctured is another characteristic separating these three species.
</paragraph>
